revision.text:
{{EngvarB|date=April 2014}}
{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2014}}
The '''2013 drought in Maharashtra''' in [[India]] came about after the region received lower rainfall during the [[monsoon]] season June to September 2012. It is considered as the region's worst drought in 40 years. The worst-hit areas in [[Maharashtra]] were [[Solapur district|Solapur]], [[Parbhani district|Parbhani]], [[Ahmednagar district|Ahmednagar]], [[Sangli district|Sangli]], [[Pune district|Pune]], [[Satara district|Satara]], [[Beed district|Beed]] and [[Nashik district|Nashik]]. Residents of [[Latur district|Latur]], [[Osmanabad district|Osmanabad]], [[Nanded district|Nanded]], [[Aurangabad district, Bihar|Aurangabad]], [[Jalna district|Jalna]], [[Jalgaon district|Jalgaon]] and [[Dhule district|Dhule]] districts were also affected by this [[famine]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Maharashtra reels under worst drought in 40 years|url=http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/slideshow/18969670.cms|accessdate=31 March 2013|newspaper=The Economic Times|date=14 March 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Maharashtra faces drought as opposition alleges mismanagement|url=http://www.livemint.com/Politics/pvkfJrd1C2WRX2P1RELepJ/Maharashtra-faces-drought-as-opposition-alleges-mismanagemen.html|accessdate=31 March 2013|newspaper=live mint|date=16 January 2013}}</ref>

