{{Infobox civil conflict | title = 2014 Albanian demonstrations in Macedonia | partof = | image = | caption = | date = 4 July 2014 - 11 July 2014 <ref>https://photos.state.gov/libraries/macedonea/552353/ArchivePDFsJuly2014/Demo%20Notice-July%204%202014.pdf</ref> | place = {{flag|Macedonia}}, mostly in North-west region | coordinates = | causes = * Operation "Monster" ** Sentence to life imprisonment of six ethnic Albanians * Ethnic discrimination | goals = * Liberation of the convicted persons * Implementation of [[Ohrid Agreement]] * Ethnic equality | methods = * Protests * Civil disobedience * Demonstrations * Online activism | status = | result = | side1 = {{flagicon|Albania}} [[Ethnic Albanians]] | side2 = {{flagicon|Macedonia}} [[Government of Macedonia]] | side3 = | leadfigures1 = | leadfigures2 = [[Nikola Gruevski]] | leadfigures3 = | howmany1 = | howmany2 = | howmany3 = | casualties1 = | casualties2 = | casualties3 = | fatalities = | injuries = | arrests = | detentions = | charged = | fined = | casualties_label = | notes = }}
The '''2014 Albanian demonstrations in Macedonia''' were series of protests in cities populated with [[Albanians in Macedonia|Albanians]] in [[Republic of Macedonia|Macedonia]], following the sentence to life imprisonment of six ethnic Albanians, related to [[Smilkovci lake killings]] and the Operation "Monster".<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://almakos.com/lajme/maqedoni/54730-monstra-shperthejne-lotet-ne-gjykate-pas-denimit-me-burg-te-perjetshem-video.html |title=Monstra: Shpërthejnë lotët në gjykatë, pas dënimit me burg të përjetshëm (VIDEO) |access-date=2014-07-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714225203/http://almakos.com/lajme/maqedoni/54730-monstra-shperthejne-lotet-ne-gjykate-pas-denimit-me-burg-te-perjetshem-video.html |archive-date=2014-07-14 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref>
==Background== {{See also|Smilkovci lake killings|2012 Republic of Macedonia inter-ethnic violence}}
==Protests== The first protest took place on 4 July in Caircanka area of [[Skopje]], after the [[Jum'ah]] prayer.<ref>https://photos.state.gov/libraries/macedonea/552353/ArchivePDFsJuly2014/Demo%20Notice-July%204%202014.pdf</ref> There were about 9,000 peoples involved in the protest and several participants and police were injured.{{citation needed|date=December 2014}} On 5 July, protest took place the afternoon of in the [[Čair Municipality|Čair]] and the Caircanka areas of Skopje<ref>https://photos.state.gov/libraries/macedonea/552353/ArchivePDFsJuly2014/Demo%20Notice-July%205%202014.pdf</ref> Demonstrations that took place on 6 July were in the following cities: Skopje, Debar, Gostivar, Kicevo, Kumanovo, Ohrid, Struga and Tetovo.<ref>https://photos.state.gov/libraries/macedonea/552353/ArchivePDFsJuly2014/Demo%20Notice-July%206%202014.pdf</ref> On 11 July, the protesters were gathered at the Jaja Pasha Mosque in Skopje, after the Friday prayer and continued towards the Courthouse. There were more than 10,000 protesters gathered in this day.{{citation needed|date=December 2014}}
