{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2017}} {{Infobox Magazine | image_file = | image_size = | image_caption = | publisher = | total_circulation = | circulation_year = | category = Theater magazine | frequency = Bi-monthly | editor= | editor_title = | founder = | language = [[Spanish language|Spanish]] | country = [[Spain]] | based = [[Madrid]] | founded = 1957 | firstdate = | finaldate = | website = [http://www.primeracto.com/ ''Primer Acto''] | issn = 0032-8367 | oclc = 825181 }} '''''Primer Acto''''' is a [[Spanish language|Spanish]] bi-monthly theater magazine based in [[Madrid, Spain]].
==History and profile== ''Primer Acto'' was established in 1957.<ref name="rc">{{cite news|title=Primer Acto|url=http://www.revistasculturales.com/revistas/50/primer-acto/|accessdate=4 February 2017|work=Revistas Culturales}}</ref> It was started as a successor to ''Teatro'', which existed from 1952 to 1957.<ref name="jon">{{cite book|author=John London|title=Reception and Renewal in Modern Spanish Theatre, 1939-1963|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=hQLnqUx4NpkC&pg=PA149|accessdate=4 February 2017|year=1997|publisher=MHRA|isbn=978-0-901286-83-3|page=149}}</ref> The magazine is published on a bi-monthly basis and covers [[Latin American]] and Spanish theatre.<ref name="rc"/> José Monleón is the director of the magazine, which is headquartered in Madrid.<ref name="rc"/> One of the earlier directors was José Monleon.<ref>{{cite book|author=Jo Labanyi|title=A Companion to Spanish Cinema|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=1oxXCQAAQBAJ&pg=PA457|accessdate=4 February 2017|date=21 December 2015|publisher=John Wiley & Sons|isbn=978-1-119-17013-6|page=457}}</ref> José Luis Alonso is among the former editors.<ref name=jon/> At the beginning of the 1960s the members of the editorial board included [[Arnold Wesker]] and [[Kenneth Tynan]].<ref name=jon/>
