{{third-party|date=August 2018}} {{notability|Companies|date=May 2018}} {{Infobox school | name = Rainbow High School | motto = | seal_image = | image = | image size = | alt = | other_names = Rainbow | caption = | established = 1998 | type = Private | locale = Urban | grades = | head_name = Headmaster | head = | head_name2 = Exam board | head2 = | city = [[Gaborone]], [[Botswana]] | state = | country = [[Botswana]] | coordinates = {{coord|24|39|29|S|25|54|44|E|region:BW}} | students = | school_colors = Black, Grey, Blue and White | website = {{URL|http://www.rainbowschool.ac.bw}} | footnotes = <ref name="home"/> }}
'''Rainbow High School''' is a private,<ref name="your botswana"/> co-educational, inter-denominational school located in [[Gaborone|Gaborone city]], [[Botswana]]. It was opened in 1998. The school comprises a primary school<ref name="your botswana">https://yourbotswana.com/index.php/2018/03/11/parents-feel-the-pinch-as-private-school-fees-soar/</ref>, [[middle school | preparatory (middle) school]], and a [[high school]].<ref name="home">{{cite web|work=Rainbow School official website | title=Rainbow School | url=http://www.rainbowschool.ac.bw/home.php?s=1 | location=Botswana | accessdate=10 October 2017}}</ref>
==History== The school began as a primary school in 1997 with one form, and then in 1998 it opened a high school.<ref name="home" /><ref>{{cite web|title=Rainbow Primary 1997|url=https://directory.justlanded.com/en/Education_International-schools/Rainbow-English-Medium-Secondary-School-Gaborone | work=Just Landed | accessdate=10 October 2017}}</ref> The school initially had capacity for 75 students and had only seven teachers. The school now has more than 600 students and more than 50 staff.<ref name="home" />
==Facilities== Facilities include a 600-seat hall, a gym, a library, five laboratories and specialist classrooms for computer application technology, consumer studies, music and art. The computer labs and some classrooms have [[Asymmetric Digital Subscriber Line|ADSL]] internet connections.{{cn|date=August 2018}}
==Haircut controversy== In 2007, the school caused controversy by sending a memo to parents of black students informing them that [[afro]] haircuts would not be allowed.<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.weekendpost.co.bw/wp-column-details.php?col_id=771 | title=The Afro issue, an insult to Africans | work=WeekendPost | location=Botswana | publisher=ATD Media Corporation | first=Gasebalwe | last=Seretse | date=September 25, 2017 | access-date=August 19, 2018 }}</ref> The school reversed the decision after an intervention by actor [[Donald Molosi]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thegazette.news/rainbow-reinstates-afro-hairstyles-after-donald-molosi-intervention/|title=Rainbow reinstates Afro hairstyles after Donald Molosi intervention|work=[[The Botswana Gazette]] |dead-url=yes|date=2017-09-21|quote=Rainbow High School in Gaborone has been challenged by members of the public to issue an apology after reversing its ...|archive-url=http://webcache.googleusercontent.com/search?q=cache:E7ks3MuCRqcJ:www.thegazette.news/rainbow-reinstates-afro-hairstyles-after-donald-molosi-intervention/+&cd=1&hl=en&ct=clnk&gl=je|archive-date=17 August 2018}}</ref>
